Not really. I just know that you are overrating the difference that much int makes really. Not enough to call it a sacrifice by any means. If that were the case, everyone would be 'sacrificing' because they weren't playing Erudites. It might mean you have roughly 100 mana less in the long run if you never max your int, but I don't really consider that anywhere near 'sacrifice' level. Too much int gear in the game these days, at all levels to even think that. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
