<br>
355int(even buffless, and I always use voq)<br>
305sta<br>
<br>
Personally, I think that the int would be a better choice because it'd facilitate your climb to level 65. more int, more mana pool- in general you'd have an easier time of getting to 65 with quadding. mana pool is rather essential for that pursuit. as for the extra hps, it doesn't really do any good unless youre raiding. in that case, the whole Luclin era is rather bereft of nasty AEs, but that changes in the elementals. the extra HPs is sure handy, but even now I'm capped to sta with buffs.<br>
<br>
so you have the choice then. for a few extra hps later, you have a harder time of leveling to it. I don't see how the hps are THAT useful to a wizard, and in retrospect I think the extra int that helped me get to 65 quickly here was probably worth it. if you're going to quad without serious twinking to 255 int, then I suggest you invest in int. otherwise, the 355 is rather easy to reach with ubergear anywya. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyron>Kyron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 312<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/25/03 9:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: high end</span><hr size=1> If you are gonna twink your toon its pretty easy to max out your int with wizzy gear. In that case I'd actually say, go for the STA. If you are not gonna twink, I'd say the Int is a must. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/03 3:02 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: high end</span><hr size=1> olden day wizards could quad with ~200 int and no breeze/c/c2/c3/c4/c5... Int isn't that important anymore especially since KEI gives you 25. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompil